<!-- 2.1 About Page with Data Sources -->
<div class="row">
  <div class="col-lg-8 mx-auto">
    <h1 class="mb-4">About Climate Weather Tracker</h1>

    <section class="mb-5">
      <h2>Project Overview</h2>
      <p>Climate Weather Tracker is a comprehensive web application designed to track and analyze weather conditions
        across different cities and climate zones worldwide. This application provides users with detailed weather
        readings, climate zone classifications, and weather condition information.</p>
    </section>

    <section class="mb-5">
      <h2>Data Sources</h2>
      <div class="card mb-3">
        <div class="card-header bg-primary text-white">
          <h4 class="mb-0">Climate Classification Data (CSV)</h4>
        </div>
        <div class="card-body">
          <p><strong>Source:</strong> Köppen Climate Classification System</p>
          <p><strong>Description:</strong> Climate zones are categorized based on the Köppen climate classification,
            which divides climates into five main groups based on temperature and precipitation patterns.</p>
          <p><strong>Fields:</strong> zone name, zone description, and standardized zone codes</p>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="card mb-3">
        <div class="card-header bg-success text-white">
          <h4 class="mb-0">Cities in Canada (JSON)</h4>
        </div>
        <div class="card-body">
          <p><strong>Source:</strong>https://simplemaps.com/data/canada-cities</p>
          <p><strong>Description:</strong> comprehensive city information including location coordinates
            (latitude/longitude) and country classifications.</p>
          <p><strong>Fields:</strong> city name, country, coordinates for mapping</p>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="card mb-3">
        <div class="card-header bg-info text-white">
          <h4 class="mb-0">Weather Condition Data (CSV)</h4>
        </div>
        <div class="card-body">
          <p><strong>Source:</strong> https://openweathermap.org/weather-conditions</p>
          <p><strong>Description:</strong> Standardized weather condition classifications including sunny, cloudy,
            rainy, snowy, and other atmospheric conditions.</p>
          <p><strong>Fields:</strong> condition codes, condition names, condition descriptions, and icon references</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="card mb-3">
        <div class="card-header bg-warning">
          <h4 class="mb-0">Daily Weather Data (JSON)</h4>
        </div>
        <div class="card-body">
          <p><strong>Source:</strong>
            https://api.openweathermap.org//data/2.5/forecast/daily?lat={latitude}&lon={longitude}&units=metric&cnt=16&appid=4b2047652a8cb49876e5a83394ffe24f
          </p>
          <p><strong>Description:</strong> Real-time and historical weather readings including temperature, humidity,
            wind speed, and other meteorological measurements.</p>
          <p><strong>Fields:</strong> Daily temperature, min/max temperatures, wind speed, humidity, timestamp</p>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="card mb-3">
        <div class="card-header bg-black text-white">
          <h4 class="mb-0">Classify the City (JSON)</h4>
        </div>
        <div class="card-body">
          <p><strong>Source:</strong> http://climateapi.scottpinkelman.com/api/v1/location/{latitude}/{longitude}</p>
          <p><strong>Description:</strong> use `latitude` and `longitude` to classify cities into a climate zone via
            API.</p>
          <p><strong>Fields:</strong> climate classification codes </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="mb-5">
      <h2>Entity Relationship Diagram</h2>
      <div class="card">
        <%= image_tag("er_diagram.png", class: "card-img-top", alt: "...") %>
        <div class="card-body">
          <p>The application database is structured around four main entities:</p>
          <ul>
            <li><strong>Climate Zones:</strong> Categories that classify different climate types</li>
            <li><strong>Cities:</strong> Geographic locations where weather is tracked</li>
            <li><strong>Weather Conditions:</strong> Standardized weather state classifications</li>
            <li><strong>Weather Readings:</strong> Individual measurements of weather data</li>
          </ul>

          <h5 class="mt-3">Key Relationships:</h5>
          <ul>
            <li>Cities belong to Climate Zones (many-to-many through city_climates)</li>
            <li>Weather Readings belong to Cities (one-to-many)</li>
            <li>Weather Readings categorized by Weather Conditions (many-to-one)</li>
          </ul>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h2>Technical Stack</h2>
      <p>This application is built using:</p>
      <ul>
        <li>Ruby on Rails 8+</li>
        <li>Bootstrap 5 for responsive design</li>
        <li>Kaminari gem for pagination</li>
        <li>Google Maps API for location visualization</li>
      </ul>
    </section>
  </div>
</div>